        return EmployeeList.FromEnumerable(filteredEmployees);
    }

    private IEnumerable<Employee> FilterEmployees(IEnumerable<IEmployee> employees)
    {
        // elided
    }
}

```

Basically this is how I understood Ports and Adapters as [proposed by Alistair Cockburn](http://alistair.cockburn.us/Hexagonal+architecture). Anyway, this implementation somehow contradicts the Mark Seeman quote (see above), since `App` depends bot on the `IEmployeeRepository` *and* the `IEmployeeListProvider` ports. Of course it would be possible to restructure the design to use a filter port

```
